sql:
SELECT subregion_name 
FROM subregions 
WHERE population_density > 250 AND area_km2 < 1000;

external_knowledge:
The term "year that just passed the 2020 mark" refers to the year 2020; "sex ratio" indicates the ratio of males to females; "gender and age group" include categories such as male, female, and different age brackets (e.g., 0, 1_4, 5_9).;
Subregion refers to a smaller geographical division within a larger region.;
Average sex ratio is calculated by averaging the sex ratios across multiple data points for the same subregion, gender, and age group.

